### **1. ZIP Deployment Script & Generate Gist**  
**Instructions** to generate the ZIP and create a GitHub Gist:

1. **Clone and build the ZIP file**:
```bash
#!/bin/bash

# Create the deployment structure
mkdir -p repo-templates/{blockchain-for-faith,bible-validate,verse-studio,faith-ai,sacred-ipfs}/.github/workflows
mkdir -p repo-templates/{blockchain-for-faith,bible-validate,verse-studio,faith-ai,sacred-ipfs}/.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE

# Populate template files (use previous files from this thread or manually add)

# Generate minimal content for first folder
echo "MIT License" > repo-templates/blockchain-for-faith/LICENSE
echo "FROM rust:..." > repo-templates/blockchain-for-faith/Dockerfile
echo "CraftScript..." > repo-templates/blockchain-for-faith/.github/workflows/ci.yml
echo "Contributing..." > repo-templates/blockchain-for-faith/CONTRIBUTING.md

# Create ZIP
zip -r repo-templates.zip repo-templates/

# Optional: Host as Gist
# Login to GitHub via CLI and create gist
# Or use: https://gist.github.com
```

