### **2. GitHub Authenticated Bash Script**  
Enhance deployment script with authentication and error handling:

```bash
#!/bin/bash

# --- Authentication ---
GITHUB_USER="codeximmortal"
GITHUB_TOKEN="ghp_XXXXXXXXXX"  # Replace with Git token (https://github.com/settings/tokens)
REPOS=("blockchain-for-faith" "bible-validate" "verse-studio" "faith-ai" "sacred-ipfs")

# --- Deploy Logic ---
cd repo-templates/
for REPO in "${REPOS[@]}"; do
  echo " Deploying $REPO..."
  git init
  git add .
  git commit -m "${REPO} initial deploy"
  git remote add origin "https://${GITHUB_TOKEN}@github.com/${GITHUB_USER}/${REPO}.git"
  git push -f origin main || git push -f origin master || echo "Push manual needed (check permissions)"
  echo " Repo created at: https://github.com/${GITHUB_USER}/${REPO}"
  cd ..
done

echo "âœ… Automated deployment complete (use 'chmod +x deploy.sh' before execution)."
```

